Improved Intercept		KEY:Archery Talent ~ Improved Intercept		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary		PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Archer,10	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Archery Talent ~ Intercept Arrow								DESC:When the archer takes a full-attack action with a ranged weapon, he can choose to forgo one of his attacks. If he does so, he can use his intercept arrow talent as an immediate action instead of a readied action at any time before his next turn. His attack roll to intercept uses the same bonuses as the attack he chose to forgo during his previous action.
Intercept Arrow			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Intercept Arrow		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary		PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Archer,4																				DESC:An archer can ready a ranged attack to deflect a ranged weapon attack against him or an ally within 30 feet. To deflect the attack, the archer makes an attack with a ranged weapon. If his attack roll is greater than the attacking opponent’s roll, the opponent’s initial attack automatically misses. For each size category the attacking creature is larger than the archer, he takes a –4 penalty on his attack roll. The archer must declare the use of this talent after the attack is announced, but before the roll is made. Unusually massive ranged weapons, such as boulders or ballista bolts, and ranged attacks by firearms or generated by natural attacks or spell effects can’t be deflected.
Long Strides			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Long Strides			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																												DESC:An archer with this talent increases his movement speed by 10 feet if he is wearing light armor or no armor. If he has a natural Fly, Climb, or Swim Speed, it increases by 10 feet as well.																																																																																																		BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10|!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy,TYPE=Armor.Medium	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Fly|10|PREMULT:2,[!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy,TYPE=Armor.Medium],[PREMOVE:1,Fly=1]	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Climb|10|PREMULT:2,[!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy,TYPE=Armor.Medium],[PREMOVE:1,Climb=1]	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Swim|10|PREMULT:2,[!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy,TYPE=Armor.Medium],[PREMOVE:1,Swim=1]
Marauder's Step			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Marauder's Step		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary		PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Archer,8	PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge,Mobility,Shot on the Run										DESC:Whenever the archer uses a full-round action to full-attack with a ranged weapon, he may move up to half his speed as a free action before the first attack is made. This can provoke attacks of opportunity normally. The benefits of this ability apply only when he wears light or no armor. He loses all benefits of this ability when wearing medium or heavy armor, or carrying a medium or heavy load.
Nowhere to Run			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Nowhere to Run			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Archery Talent ~ Hunter's Target								DESC:Once per turn, whenever an opponent whom the archer selected for his Hunter's Target attempts to withdraw (whether from the archer or an ally), he can make an Attack of Opportunity against that target.
Piercing Shot			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Piercing Shot			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary																												DESC:The archer may use this talent as a standard action to make a single ranged attack at his full attack bonus with his bow or crossbow. Instead of attacking a specific target, the projectile affects all creatures in a single line, originating from the archer and going out a distance equal to the range increment of the weapon he uses. This attack applies to each target in the line, hitting each target whose AC he beats with his attack roll and dealing normal damage (plus the effects of any special properties on the projectile). If a critical hit is confirmed, the archer critically hits only the first target struck in the line.
