Reset Initiative			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Reset Initiative		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Archery Talent ~ Expert Initiative							DESC:Once per encounter, as a free action at any time after the first round (that is, the first full round after the surprise Round, if one occurs), the archer can set his Initiative Count to his current Initiative +5 for the rest of the encounter.
Saving Grace			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Saving Grace			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																												DESC:An archer that selects this talent can select one aimed target per encounter and add a +%1 insight bonus to all saving throws that he makes when targeted by an attack or ability used by his aimed target. This is also doubled by Take Aim at 13th.|ArcherAimedTargetBonus																																																																																					ASPECT:SaveBonus|+%1 insight bonus to all saving throws that he makes when targeted by an attack or ability used by his aimed target.|ArcherAimedTargetBonus
Second Chance Shot		KEY:Archery Talent ~ Second Chance Shot		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																												DESC:When he misses with a ranged attack, the archer may reroll his attack at a –5 penalty. Using this ability is an immediate action.
Secondary Target			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Secondary Target		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary		PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Archer,14																				DESC:The archer’s incredible skill with bows or crossbows means that even failure is success. Whenever the archer misses his target with a ranged attack, he may redirect the attack to an enemy within 20 feet of his target. He makes an attack roll against the new target, and if successful, hits as if he had targeted them in the first place. The archer may use this ability as often as he misses, but once he hits a creature with a redirected attack, he cannot target it again this way until the beginning of his next turn. 
Shared Precision			KEY:Archery Talent ~ Shared Precision		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArcheryTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Precise Shot													DESC:When an archer hits a creature with a ranged attack, he grants his allies within 10 feet of her the benefit of the Precise Shot feat against that target until the start of his next turn. His allies must remain within 10 feet of him, and must be able both to see and hear the archer to gain this benefit.
